### take() {#a209e0c1acaf944e5ffd792ef85742506}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static std::pair&lt; instrprof&#95;error, std::string &gt; llvm::InstrProfError::take (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">Error</a> E)</>}
  labels = {["inline", "static"]}>
Consume an <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">Error</a> and return the raw enum value contained within it, and the optional error message.

The <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">Error</a> must either be a success value, or contain a single <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/instrproferror">InstrProfError</a>.
